deck_excerpt: Ryu Okami combo deck
deck_description:
A crazy combo deck which consistently leads to a board with Saryuja Skull Dread, Lord Of The Red, ABC - Dragon Buster, Invoked Mechaba, Ancient Gear Megaton Golem and Chimeratech Rampage Dragon. The deck works by giving Ryu Okami to your opponent through Summon Sorceress and milling Cyber Dragon Nova to special summon machine fusion monsters from the extra deck. The deck won't work if the opponent's zones in front of the extra monster zones are occupied or if either Summon Sorceress or Ryu Okami get negated. Having Ryu Okami in your hand is mandatory for the deck to work: destroy Mariamne with Diagram or another Mariamne to search it out. Second step is to summon Summon Sorceress, which you can do in three ways
  • discard Rosenix or Thystvern to special summon Sulfefnir, destroy it with its effect to summon Citree and use Rosenix's token or Thystvern's search to go into Needlefiber, use its effect to special summon another Citree and go into Sorceress;
  • special summon Terrortop and bring out Taketomborg, then summon any Crystron and go directly into Sorceress;
  • summon a True King and Al-Lumi'raj to go Needlefiber -> Citree -> Sorceress; Al-Lumi'raj can be brought out by destroying Bahrastos.
Now the combo begins: special summon Ryu Okami to your opponent's field with Sorceress' first effect, then use its second effect to bring out a True King: this way Ryu will start milling your Extra Deck. Megaton is a big beater, Mechaba negates, ABC banishes, Chimeratech dumps ABC's materials and attacks multiple times, Omega recycles Nova and Herald, Herald searches Lord Of The Red and Advanced Ritual Art, Nova summons fusions (except ABC) and Saryuja and Goblin expand your Extra Monster Zones.

deck_excerpt: Mekk-Knight Kaiju OTK (Going Second)
deck_description: Finally I have finished this deck. First of all, this deck is so much fun to play in my opinion so please enjoy the deck! I have play tested this deck so much from scratch and it has become really good. I was able to beat Trickstar Sky Striker three times in a row with this deck and many other meta and tier two decks. The goal of the deck is to always go second and special summon Kaijus to your opponents field in the same column as their spell/traps are and then special summon Mekk-Knights! Psi-Blocker is super helpful too to block off cards your opponent needs to win once you know what deck they are playing. Use Ghost Reaper & Winter Cherries to dominate meta players and make them banish their core pieces. Waking The Dragon is really good to side in against decks that like removing your backrow. Once they try to remove it they will be stuck with Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon on your side of the field and that will win you the game! Spell Absorption is a spicy tech card I threw in to help counter Trickstars and Chain Burn since they inflict so much damage. One awesome combo I love to do is special summon Mekk-Knight Blue Sky and then normal summon Cherries or Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring and synchro into PSY-Framelord Omega. Hope you enjoy!

deck_excerpt: Burning Abyss Synchro Turbo Deck 2018
deck_description: After making many Burning Abyss builds from scratch trying to create spicy techs this is the one I have made as the final product. It never bricks and can go first or second. Going second is better though since this build runs a lot of handtraps for many reasons. The ghost girls are used to stop your opponent from doing pretty much everything, not only are they good handtraps but you can use them as synchro material with the other Burning Abyss monsters so they aren't bricks in your hand your upcoming turn! That is why this build plays three Libic, Malebranche of the Burning Abyss so that you can send Libic to the graveyard and use his effect to special summon a Burning Abyss monster from your hand and negate its effects. This way you can normal summon a ghost girl and go into Brionac, Dragon of the Ice Barrier or Gravity Warrior which is another cool tech I added in. Gravity Warrior is good to use when you're opponent has a lot of monsters on their board and you don't have access to Black Luster Soldier. Since Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit and Effect Veiler are light monsters, they can be used as material for Black Luster Soldier. Also, Virgil isn't dead! Synchro into Virgil, Rock Star of the Burning Abyss in this build using Rubic, Malebranche of the Burning Abyss and the other Burning Abyss monsters. Virgil's shuffle effect is very powerful even in today's meta. After testing I have won games because of Virgil! Enjoy the deck and have fun guys.

deck_excerpt: A simple Fluffal deck that's very cheap but also pretty effective.
deck_description: Main Deck: 3x Edge Imp Tomahawk: Can turn itself into any “edge imp” card. Summon with Sheep instead of normal summoning if possible. Price: $0.14  3x Edge Imp Chain: Searches a fusion card or counter trap when sent to the graveyard. Also necessary for a very good fusion monster. Price: $0.05  3x Edge Imp Sabres: Necessary for almost all the fusions we do, and it can revive itself too boot. Price: $0.15  3x Fluffal Owl: Searches Polymerization, and can fuse by itself if needed. Price: $0.10  3x Fluffal Sheep: Allows us to use Edge Imp monster’s effects more often. Very good for late-game. Price: $0.09  3x Fluffal Cat: Recycles our Polymerizations. Price: $0.05  3x Fluffal Rabbit: Recycles our Fluffal and Edge Imp monsters. Price: $0.07  3x Frightfur Fusion: Late-game fusion that allows for massive otk’s and board wipes with Frightfur Wolf and Tiger. Price: $0.12  3x Polymerization: Unfortunately, this card is necessary in order for us to summon anything. Don’t waste any. Price: $0.57  1x Dark Hole: Wipes both player’s boards. Good for when you’re behind drastically. Price: $0.08  3x Suture Rebirth: Allows us to recover beaters after a couple turns. If used on Frightfur Sheep, the resurrection effect still works! Price: $0.09  2x Night Beam: Spell and Trap destruction, used in any decent deck-build. Price: $0.16  2x Fluffal Crane: Deck thinning, allowing us to recover from our opponent destroying our on-board fusion material. Price: $0.06  2x Mirror Force: One of the best monster removal cards at this price range. Price: $0.20  3x Frightfur March: Helps our Frightfur monsters stay alive longer. Price: $0.10  Extra Deck:  1x Frightfur Chimera: Our target for Frightfur March. Has a very big body and can give decent rewards since the card you resummon doesn’t have its effects negated. Price: $0.05  2x Frightfur Wolf: OTK machine. 4 Materials = 8000 damage to face. Also very nice for OTK through low ATK boards. Price: $0.08  2x Frightfur Tiger: Most of the time, this will nuke all the cards your opponent can use. Just think carefully about what you choose. Price: $0.20  2x Frightfur Sheep: Very durable monster that can be buffed to insane levels. Keep in mind that  when resurrected it will move out of the extra monster zone and into the main monster zone. Price: $0.10   2x Space Insulator: Great vertical arrows that can be made with anything. Make this card first before other Link monsters. Price: $0.01

deck_excerpt: A budget metalfoes deck good for those who want a good quality starter deck.
deck_description:
Main Deck:

The next few cards are metalfoes’ normal monster lineup. Their pendulum effects are all the same, so the only details I’ll leave is where their preferred location is.

3x Metalfoes Volflame: In Extra deck Price: $0.11

 

3x Metalfoes Goldriver: In Extra deck Price: $0.24

 

3x Metalfoes Silverd: On Pendulum Zone Price: $0.10

3x Metalfoes Steelen: On Pendulum Zone Price: $0.03

 

3x Rescue Rabbit: Best card in the deck, hands-down. Allows a free link monster and if you have a 1 and 8-scale pendulum monster in hand, a fusion monster. Just make sure to play other cards so that you can bait out any negations the opponent might have. Price: $0.50

 

3x Archfiend Eccentrick: Spell, Trap, and Monster removal in one card! Price: $0.12

 

3x Raremetalfoes Bismugear: If it gets destroyed by your opponent or your own card (likely other Metalfoes monsters) Price: $0.05

 

3x Painful Decision: Searches out any Metalfoes monster while filling our graveyard for Mithrillium. Price: $0.13

 

1x Dark Hole: Great board wipe. Price: $0.10

 

3x Metalfoes Fusion: Our main fusion card. Can recycle for draw power if needed. Price: $0.10

 

3x Fullmetalfoes Fusion: Fusion summons on your opponent’s turn! Most of the time, you will be summoning Fullmetalfoes Alkahest with this card. Price: $0.04

 

3x Metalfoes counter: Brings out monsters to replace our dead ones.Price: $0.02

 

3x Dimension Guardian: This card protects our monsters from most threats. Especially useful on link monsters. Price: $0.10

 

3x Metalfoes Combination: With this, we can use a card for fusion material in the hand, then place it back on the field. Or, fusion summon any level 7 or lower fusion monster, then use it to summon Orichalc and bring it right back. Price: $0.06

 

Extra Deck:

 

2x Metalfoes Orichalc: Big body that can damage your opponent through defense monsters. Also high leveled for combination plays. Price: $0.03

2x Metalfoes Mithrilium: Recycles cards and removes monsters all at the same time. Price: $0.10

1x Metalfoes Adamante: (Almost) guaranteed target for fusion with Alkahest’s effect. Price: $0.03

2x Fullmetalfoes Alkahest: Steals opponent’s monsters in the middle of their plays, stopping them in their tracks. You can also summon fusion monsters with the monsters you stole, allowing greater board presence on the next turn. Price: $0.10

1x Zefra Metaltron: Using a Chimera and 2 Metalfoes monsters, you can summon a monster which can remove your opponent’s monsters temporarily and recycle resources when your opponent removes a Metalfoes monster. Price: $0.09

 

2x Do-little Chimera: Our main link monster. Gives our Metalfoes an attack boost and can add either itself or a Metalfoes from the Graveyard into your hand upon death. Price: $0.10

deck_excerpt: Hate Blue-Eyes users? Don't want to spend hundred$ on a deck like them? Use this deck to end them all! Laugh in their face as they sit contemplating t
deck_description: This deck is based on cards I actually have. Keep that, and the fact that the fanboy in me shows, in mind. For example, there is only one Buster Dragon because they cost +$6 each. Also, there is a majestic dragon in there because I am a fanboy. This deck is able to run relatively well without spending $100.  I personally find it fun to use. Of course, the main idea is to summon the Buster Blader fusion and Buster Dragon so your opponents monsters are all stuck in defense and unable to use effects. There are other options like Dark Paladin, and the Ebon Magicians, which are both easy to summon with this deck. Number 11 is always nice to have and it is very easy to summon in this deck. Just for extra fun there is the Stardust option and Beelze. Great fun to play a Blue-eyes fanboy and do 10,000 plus damage on a Chaos Max stuck in defense. Any feedback is welcome.  P.S. - I don't use link or pendulum monsters

Third: Although less used is an anti-xyz deck, using effects of the opponent's monster with Number 8: Heraldic King Genom-Heritage and leaving defenseless STRONG POINT: the key card of the deck and send the heraldic beast leo in the cemetery as possible to seek some other for the hand (preferred heraldic beast amphisbaena) and different from many XYZ decks and greater advantage on the deck and use all xyz materials and renew they use " Heraldic Beast Twin-Headed Eagle" to use again 2 materials from cemitery WEAK POINT: As it is a deck that uses effects from the monsters of the cemetery to be able to remove them later or bring them back, if the opponent uses removals, the deck literally dies ... Side deck: You can opt for a "Utopia deck" since it makes xyz quickly and buying cards by "XYZ change tactics" or use other numbers above 100 depending on the relevance P.S: I'm Brazilian, so...my English is not good.

deck_excerpt: Add Exodia Pieces from your Banished Pile by using Pot of Desires & Primal Seed.
deck_description: An Exodia FTK/OTK Build with a ton of potential, built around banishing your Exodia pieces & returning them to your hand with Primal Seed. There is room to include Called by the Grave & other Floodgates without effecting combo's. The Deck is built on 3 Combos; 1. ISOLDE: Opening up with "Armageddon Knight" will let you send "Destiny Hero - Malicious" to the GY, allowing you to Special Summon another copy to Link into Isolde. Search and add "Black Luster Soldier - Envoy of the Beginning" to your hand OR another "Armageddon Knight" if you have "Allure of Darkness"/ "Hand Destruction" in Hand. Use Isolde to send an Equip spell to the GY to special summon "Destiny Hero - Dark Angel" & if possible Special Summon another copy of Malicious. You can Link into most LINK - 4 monsters from here or into "Decode Talker" & "Linkuriboh". Also if you have a copy of One for One in hand you can Link into Saryuja. 2. SERIAL SPELL: Opening up with "Pot of Desires" & "Serial Spell" is almost always a Win. It should draw enough power to get you BLS & Primal Seed first turn, and banish enough to allow you to continue your plays with Primal Seed. 3. GRINDER GOLEM / ONE DAY OF PEACE: If you open the duel with these 2 Cards in your hand, you're almost GUARANTEED a FTK with Exodia. **The best thing about Armageddon Knight & Isolde, is you can use them to thin your deck out prior to playing big draw power cards.** Enjoy this build. I've beaten top tier decks going second & siding in 3x "Called by the Grave" instead of 1x "Dark World Dealings" | 1x "Armageddon Knight" | 1x "Serial Spell" .

deck_excerpt: A Dinosaur-Deck (Evolution Pill) which uses Volcanics for a 1-time field nuke.
deck_description:
This is a Dinosaur-Deck (Evolution Pill-based) which uses Volcanics for a 1-time field nuke (afterwards as banishing material for Double Evolution Pill). As a "Boss-monster" I use Ultimate Conductor Tyranno (UCT), which is mostly summoned by evo. pill. Evolzars are not as big, but provide protection in form of negation.
The playmakers are Oviraptor/Foolish Burial with Overtex. Banishing Giant Rex (if possible) and Oviraptor on the field provide you with materials for ranked 4 Evolzar. Foolish Burial Goods + Blaze Acc. Reload provide the fieldnuke.
The Deck is certainly not Top-Tier, but can hold its ground quite well against them if you don't brick, which does not happen too often, but drawing 3 scattershots is quite painful. A weakness of this deck is search negation/prohibition, since the deck has very low draw-power, but good searching power (Fossil Dig, Oviraptor + Overtex, Foolish Burial [Goods], and many more). It's for sure a "blast" to play with this deck. ;) Have fun! Juliner

Soul Release and Fairy Tail - Snow is also useful in removing from play your cards from your graveyard. Caius and Mobius are there to even the field mostly to remove pesky cards. deck_excerpt: 60 Card Burning Abyss Invoked (Super Fun And Meta Relevant)
deck_description: Ok, now I know what you're thinking. That this deck doesn't work well right? Well, guess again! The Invoked Engine with Burning Abyss works super well. This deck also has a very low brick rate. After building this deck from scratch, testing, and making many edits I found the ratios that work. I was able to beat many meta decks and many tier two decks. The decks goal is to go second and win in two turns, or otk on the second turn after your opponent used up all their resources their first turn to setup. Another thing to remember when playing this deck is that you need to make Dante so you can mill cards from your deck to graveyard like Fairy Tail - Snow. Snow is a big pain to deal with, so stack up your graveyard! This deck gives so many resources to you because while you have the Burning Abyss monsters in your hand or Dante on the field, you also have either a boss monster in your hand like Black Luster Soldier, Orbital Hydralander, or Aleister The Invoker which gives you even more boss monsters and resources after your opponent has run out since normally your opponent will only have one or two boss monsters after they've finished their first turn. The deck also mains many handtraps so going second is a breeze and you can make your opponent lose a lot of their resources if you play the handtraps at the correct time. Since the deck runs so many handtraps, plus having your opponents graveyard at your disposal, going into Invoked Mechaba, and Invoked Purgatrio is easy. On the other hand, if you are forced to go first by your opponent, making Invoked Caliga is very effective at stopping your opponent from doing anything monster effect related turn two. Since many of the decks monsters are dark you shouldn't have a hard time making Caliga going first. There are so many cool tech cards I added in to the deck to make it so great! Creature Swap is a great one that I love using on my opponent, and I prefer this over Mind Control because Mind Control can cause your Burning Abyss monsters to blow themselves up while Creature Swap doesn't and still allows you to use their effects after you destroy them via battle or card effect. Another amazing combo I love doing is with Tour Bus From The Underworld. This card is super effective late game because if you mill it and you've used Beatrice already, you can shuffle her back into the extra deck to make her again! I also don't like using Terraforming and Magical Meltdown in this deck because after testing I've realized that since Magical Meltdown counts as a spell card, it prevents you from special summoning the Burning Abyss monsters. Lastly, if you don't like Pot of Desires, which I do in this deck since you play so many three ofs, you can swap it out with three Allure of Darkness instead and the deck will still work well. Enjoy and have fun!

deck_excerpt: True King Dinos 2018 (Going Second) (Updated)
deck_description: I know I have already posted a True King Dino deck already, but I felt I should make another one from scratch to see if it can be anymore better and after testing I feel that this one is more updated and better than my old one. I was able to beat a lot of meta decks with this TKD build. The goal of this deck is to go second and otk them that second turn. This deck hardly ever bricks, in fact every time I've played it I've never had a bad hand. The part of the deck that I noticed it struggles with the most is dealing with backrow so to solve that problem I put a lot of backrow removal in the side deck. Red Reboot is so good in this deck since you want to go second and you can just use Red Reboot on your opponent during your first turn (second turn of the game) so they can't use backrow anymore is so good because then you can just otk them freely without worrying about all their backrow that will stop you. Set Rotation is also super effective against decks that run field spells like ABC, Lair of Darkness, Pure Dinosaurs, etc... One of my awesome spicy techs I put into the deck is Ally of Justice Catastor. If your opponent has any monster that's not dark type and is a problem for you at that moment you can use Catastor to destroy it. I also love playing this deck because going second they get otkd out of nowhere on the second turn and then don't really know what happened, it's funny. Please enjoy the deck and if you have any questions don't hesitate to ask!

deck_excerpt: THIS DECK WORKS PRETTY WELL. PLEASE GIVE FEEDBACK
deck_description:
This deck has worked fairly well for me and uses most of the Red-Eyes cards except for I think B. Chick, Darkness (love the artwork, but not worth it IMO), Metal, and vanilla.

I've been tweaking it a bit, so it's still not perfect. I've added Full Force Virus to test out sending Flare Dragon or Meteor Dragon to GY and bringing it back with Return of the Red-Eyes to eliminate low defense monsters with Deck Devastation Virus sided if I need to eliminate low attack instead.

If you want to fusion summon Archfiend Black Skull Dragon with Red-Eyes Fusion, then you're either going to want to run a single Summoned Skull or try to get Red-Eyes Archfiend of Lightning on the field. Alternatively you can just send Archfiend to the GY using Red-Eyes Insight if you have Dragon's Mirror in hand.

I also have a Red-Eyes deck that basically just dumps dragons to revive them and Divine Dragon Lord Felgrand, but it's probably a little more pricey than this one and uses fewer Red-Eyes cards.

It's a fun deck, but this is only the first draft of the deck and will likely be changed to increase consistency. As of right now, there is no side. That will be up to individual taste.

deck_excerpt: Sky Striker Invoked 2018 (Going Second)
deck_description: After testing with this deck for about a week now I have finally found the right ratios that work well. This deck is extremely overwhelming going second, so going second is your best bet at winning. I have been able to beat almost all the meta decks using this deck so it is very powerful and can win almost every time. It has has a low brick rate. The goal of the deck is simple, to go second and handtrap your opponent when they are going first and then use their graveyard and/or your handtraps in your hand or grave for Invoked fusion material. You also have the Sky Striker cards at your disposal to draw more cards and use Sky Striker Ace - Kagari as fusion material for Invoked Purgatrio. Set Rotation is really great to screw decks that use a field spell and it's also another Terraforming basically because you want spell cards in your grave to use the second effect of the Sky Striker cards. Some games I've even been able to get Decode Talker plus two Invoked Mechabas or an Invoked Mechaba and an Invoked Purgatrio depending on how many Invocations I have in hand. This deck is also really good to bait your opponent into wasting their handtraps on the wrong cards e.g. when you have Aleister The Invoker in your hand plus Sky Stiker Mobilize - Engage! and use Engage to bait their Ash Blossom and then summon Aleister to search Invocation. Enjoy and have fun.

deck_excerpt: Consistent way of summoning Herald and Kristya ending with 4-6 cards in hand.
deck_description: GOING FIRST: 1. with gale dogra: -2 herald of the arc light in GY for 2 searches -2 lvl 6 (either herald or idaten) using benten as the tribute (searching fluffal wings the second time) -> beatrice -> toy vendor in GY -> search fluffal bear -> use fluffal bear's effect -> use toy vendor to discard fluffal wings -> use fluffal wings from GY -summon herald tributing benten -> search archlord kristya -(be sure to have 4 fairies in GY at this point) SP archlord kristya   2. without gale dogra: exactly the same as above except: -when summoning the first lvl 6 search cyber petit angel with benten -normal summon cyber petit angel -summon a link 2 using beatrice and cyber petit angel -be sure to have 4 fairies in GY at this point   3. Side decking going first: -demise, fiend of armageddon against counter traps (it can be sent to the GY via beatrice during the opponent's turn or by tributing it along with the monster you normal sumoned for a ritual summon)     GOING SECOND: 1. without side decking: -the most destructive play is: -summon natasha tributing benten (search petit angel if you don't have gale dogra) -normal summon -summon a link 2 -use natasha from grave -etc. etc. etc. depending on the situation   2. with side decking -self explanatory I guess...     NOTE: -I don't have any handtraps in the main/side deck. I suggest these: -3 called by the grave going first (droll & lock bird, artifact lancea and winter cherries are the only handtraps that can stop you) and from these only droll & ock bird is played so it is the only reason for playing called by the grave -3 infinite transcience going second: it's usefull even if you don't use it that turn (unlike gamma/veiler), it can be used more than OPT (unlike ash blossom/ghost ogre) and is the only handtrap that is unnafected by called by the grave/aqua dolphin -this isn't one of those decks that can win with 2 cards combo (except gale dogra + pre-prep or stuff like that) so it can't run many handtraps anyway. This is its biggest weakness. (more or less the weakness of all ritual decks)     OTHER SUGGESTIONS: -foolish mass burial -insect imitation (search fluffal wings normal summon it and use insect imitation to special summon gale dogra from deck) -devirituals (maybe even emergency teleport/lonefire blossom) -celestial sextant -machine angel absolute ritual (1 card board wiping combo with gale dogra, this card and vrash) -Eva (can be sent to GY with beatrice/Herald during the opponent's turn for another 2 negates or can be used for more complex combos such as summoning both watapon and lilybell or stuff like that... I used to play a herald synchro deck like that...) -herald of the orange light/the agent - earth (for summoning herald of the arc light/omega or as a hand trap) -the agent of creation - venus (there is an extra link combo with this card, idaten and machine angel absolute ritual) -galaxy soldier (infinity, or pleiades with natasha) -manju -honest -artifact lancea (handtrap in case decks that banish becomes meta) -consecrated light (side deck) -soul of purity and light -ohka -hieratics -brilliant fusion -foolish burial -kaiju/moon mirror shield (in side deck) -shaddoll dragon (beatrice target) -sandaion -time miaden -arch-airknight -phosphorage           ONLY FOR FUN SUGGESTIONS: -more copies of natasha -reasoning -monster gate -rank-up-magic - the seventh one -devirituals + mega zaborg (cannot be searched)/invicil (cannot be searched)/arcana force XXI (50/50 chances)/angel o7/vanity's ruler -goddess of sweet revenge (+fairy tail snow via beatrice) -return of the world (+ritual buster) -urgent ritual art (+ritual buster) -sprite's blessing/advanced ritual art -valkyrie of the nordic ascendant (and odin in the extra deck) -raregold armor (with natasha) -tsukumo slash (with gale dogra) -nephthys the blazing sacred phoenix/double byte dragon (if you really like this kind of cards) -xyz burst -the winged dragon of ra + immortal phoenix (if you go against players that uses sphere mode) -seraph engine (better with brilliant fusion) (YES, is just for fun, it makes the deck a lot more inconsistent!!!) -gateway to chaos -break of the world -chaos zone -mausoleum of the emperor -set rotation -monster reborn -soul charge -fulfillment of the contract -legacy of the duelist -the sanctum of parshath -light of redemption -pot of acquisitiveness -pinpoint landing -ascending soul -ritual cage -photon sanctuary -gracefull queen -vrash -vennu -dakini -tarotrei + cards like pot of the forbidden -master hyperion -arcana force 0 -lee the world chalice fairy -enrise -disserere -demolisher of rituals -breakthrough skill -instant fusion (panzer dragon and natasha into pleiades, detach natasha, etc. etc. etc.) -fusion substitute -number 29 -herald of pure light -ritual of grace -hymn of light -galaxy cyclone -shopina -mozarta -athena -jowgen/aurora paragon/barrier statue of the heavens (+machine angel ritual in grave) -banisher of the radiance -shining angel -nova summoner -nikitama -fluffal angel -super quantal fairy alphan -guiding light -double summon -chain summoning -trial and tribulation -sacred serpent's wake -ritual weapon -grisaille prison

deck_excerpt: Lightsworn Dinosaur Invoked 2018 (Smaller Version of 60 Card Decks)
deck_description: Soooooo after having this crazy theory about making Lightsworns with Dinosaurs and the Invoked engine, I brought it to life! And it's actually kinda meta. I was surprisingly able to beat a tier two deck, Cinderella, and a lot of tier one decks... I was actually able to beat Pure Dinosaurs, ABC Knightmare, and Pure Sky Strikers. The only problem with this deck is that the brick rate is moderate. You can actually draw too many monsters in your starting hand which will then cause you to lose the game. That has always been the problem when you combine multiple archetypes that are somewhat large. This deck is somewhat meta I would say tier 1.5 maybe. But in the worst case, this deck is always super fun to play against your friends as a casual deck. The goal of this deck is to otk your opponent going second or control your opponent with you going first. You pick! You want to simply mill. That is the goal, that way you can trigger cards like Performage Trick Clown, Revival Golem, Wulf, Lightsworn Beast, etc... To special summon from the graveyard so you can make a lot of link monsters or go into Minerva, the Exalted Lightsworn, or PSY-Framelord Omega, or whatever you want to play to make your opponent suffer from your deck being depleted. Double Evolution Pill kills in this deck. Being able to bait your opponent's handtraps with something like normal summoning Aleister The Invoker and then using Double Evolution Pill to get Ultimate Conductor Tyranno is amazing, or the other way around. You can also make Naturia Beast going first sometimes. If you have Giant Rex in your hand and you have Foolish Burial in your hand is you can normal summon Giant Rex and then us Foolish Burial to send Glow-Up Blub and use Glow-Up Blubs effect to send one card from your deck to grave to special summon himself. Then you can go into Naturia Beast which is basically a win condition going first since he stops all spells plus you'd have UCT. There are other ways to make Naturia Beast first turn like using Double Evolution Pill and using Giant Rex in your hand as material plus another card and get UCT and then special summon Giant Rex then you can normal summon Glow-Up Blub from your hand to get Naturia Beast. Enjoy the deck profile and as always if you have any questions or comments please write them down below or message me directly!

deck_excerpt: This deck is built for fast attacks, aggro speed. Better going second, but is fine with going first.
deck_description: This is an old deck, I'll admit. But I've tried experimenting for zoodiacs to go aggro as quick as possible, and even with a high spell count, it seems to work almost all the time. The main focus is to get either Broarbow with a ton of zoodiacs on him for direct attacks, or Anything else with protection from the mirror forces and their effects. Drident is used more of an end-game sort of card, to clear the field to attack. Overall, I really found this deck to be fun! Only edits, Maybe take out some jar of greeds for raigeki and dark hole, maybe some Xyz agents for an extra finish.

deck_excerpt: A Galaxy-Eyes deck based around both Summoning Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon and Xyz Summoning into Galaxy-Eyes Rank 8 Xyz Monsters.
deck_description:
This is my first ever Galaxy-Eyes deck, other than a rather badly failed attempt at a Galaxy-Eyes/Cipher deck, so please don't judge to harshly. As I learn more and more, I hope to keep the deck constantly updated. A few combos that could be exploited in this deck:
  1. Trade-In can send  Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon to the GY to draw 2 cards, them revive with Return of the Dragon Lords. Normal Summon Galaxy Knight using its effect, allowing for an Xyz Summon. If that Xyz Monster would be destroyed, Return of the Dragon Lords can be banished for a 1-time escape.
  2. Galaxy Soldier can send Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon to the GY, and once there Special Summons itself, and search out for Galaxy Knight. With it on the field, you can Normal Summon Galaxy Knight to Special Summon Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon from the GY, for an Xyz Summon.
  3. Photon Sanctuary can be activated in order to Special Summon 2 Photon Tokens, and with them you can Special Summon Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon. This also leaves you a Normal Summon, and with Galaxy Knight, you can Normal Summon it in order to Xyz Summon.
  I'm afraid these are the only combos I could find, but best of luck to anyone that tries out the deck, and let me know what you think of it!
